annotationA: AT26201p; Ubiquitin-protein transferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: protein polyubiquitination; Belongs to the ubiquitin-conjugating enzyme family
annotationB: Mitogen-activated protein kinase ERK-A; Serine/threonine kinase which acts as an essential component of the MAP kinase signal transduction pathway to regulate poliferation, differentiation and effect cell fate decisions in various tissues. Required downstream of phl/Raf in the sev/sevenless, tor/torso, and EGF receptor homolog Egfr signal transduction pathways. Required for embryonic epithelial tissue repair.
